  <span id="freeText6769267738910585571" style="display:none">Probably 3.5 stars. I only read the Republic, but it’s much more accessible than Plato or Aristotle, except for the fact that so many pages are missing and we only have fragments of the work. That made it hard to read and follow which opinions were his and which were the other characters in the dialogue. Some of the political theory felt rather modern, especially compared to the Ancient Greek philosophers from centuries before. It’s cool that he had more history behind him and saw more types of government work and not work. It gave me a lot to think about. But it wasn’t my favorite work of philosophy or the most insightful. </span>
